result.execSummary:
The defendant Corvelle T Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Corvelle T Williams is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Corvelle T Williams was found guilty of Felon Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

Defendant Corvelle T Williams in court with attorney Jane H Christopherson.  Defendant Corvelle T Williams in custody.  Jay R Pucek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to negotiations, the State moved to dismiss Count 1.  Court granted State's motion and ordered Count 1 dismissed.

AS TO COUNT 03:
Plea hearing proceeds. Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms or body armor.  Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.     Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 20.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 14, 2014 at 08:30 am.
At defense request and with no objection by the State, case was passed to 1:30 p.m.

Defendant Corvelle T Williams in court with attorney Jane H Christopherson.  Defendant Corvelle T Williams in custody.  Jay R Pucek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Motion hearing proceeds.  Witnesses have been sequestered.  Sworn for the State:  City of Milwaukee Police Officer Daniel Floyd.  State rests. Defense exhibit marked and referred to, but not offered, received or used.   Court has colloquy with defendant regarding his right to testify and his right not to testify; defendant advises the Court that he will not testify.  Court finds defendant has knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Defense rests.  Testimony closed. Legal arguments heard.  Court denied defense motion to suppress.  Defense counsel requested a trial date.  Court set the following:  any motions that may be filed, movant has until 5/28/14; response due by 6/17/14; reply due by 6/23/14.  All motions in limine, jury instructions and witness lists must be filed one week before the final pretrial date.  All alibi notices must be filed within statutory time periods.  Court ordered case adjourned before Branch 20  for final pretrial  on 6/30/14 at 8:30 a.m. and for jury trial on 7/14/14 at 8:30 a.m.

Attorney Jane Heather Christopherson in court, defendant Corvelle T Williams not in court, in custody.  Jay R. Pucek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Two officers needed for this hearing are unavailable on today's date (funeral; ill child).  Case is adjourned for motion hearing in Branch 20.  Motion hearing scheduled for May 8, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
